content: I don't use this App very often, but it works very well. I use it more often to monitor my WSPR signals sent from my home QTH.
works well. using on old sprint tablet with android v5
It sees that I have a radio attached, an Icom 7300 but it will not transmit.
Very good app for doing wspr from android device de NP3QL 73...
Could not change the screen size. Consequently could not read the text for setting app up.
Awesome first tx to South America.. just rocks..
Yet have good experince.
It is a great bit of software works great with my FT817.
Perfect App. I use it for wspr beacon with VOX along with HF Transceiver.
simple interface that's easy to use for a noob like me.
Love it, can't recommend it enough. So easy to use.
Download app a few days ago but couldn't get registered email not replying. So can't use.
Excellent app
Simple to use WSPR transmitter. Appears to rely on system font size being default in order to render properly but otherwise works well.

great app did have crashing problems but not moved it from back to where the app gets delivered with no issues been using it for a while it's great would love for it to listen but Tx only awsome sat in house 817 dog and wonderwand 7mhz into Europe lol great app give it a go.cannot work out framing time tho lol but certainly great to play with 10/10
Cool!
Works great for what it is. Would be cool to have receive capability too.
works for me!!
Used today for first time got great results, so easy to set up and use.
Outstanding!
Did not work with call signs that start with S5... Waiting for update
Really useful app. Works perfectly. Now I no longer need a PC for antenna testing. Many thanks Andrea de VA3KOT.

This system is the best to analyze both propagation and antenna efficiency. I'm planning on setting up 2 or more antennas and transmitters at a time but to test antenna efficiency under identical band conditions. Doesn't get any better than that.
Awesome app! Highly reccomend APRS Droid! It keeps me connected in the backcountry. ...We want a Winlink RMS Radio Email app! Please! I'd make it but I'm not smart enough hahhaha!!!!

Great App! Simple to use and very effective. I set this up on a Huawei tablet with a usb sound card and an OTG cable with my uBITX radio and I've had my signal heard in, amongst other places, Brazil, Antarctica and Tasmania.... All with 2 Watts or less. The only thing that could make this better was if it could receive and decode WSPR signals...but I've given the App 5 stars because it deserves it. Looking forward to using this mobile...üëç
works perfectly!!!
Would be a 5 if it didn't abort from time to time
Love ‚ò∫
Works great! Super easy to use. Fun! -KI7ONN

Excellent, love it! Worked almost out of the box with my FT-818 and an 80cm 
diameter magnetic loop. 73 MM0DQM
Awesome app for an awesome device

Thanks for a very useful app for qrp use in the field.  One minor, but significant, criticism for improvement on my Samsung Galaxy S5:  1. it is impossible to read the yellow label "Tune" on the white button next to START (bottom right of main screen) 2. The FREQUENCY adjustment slider is difficult to make fine adjustments 3. The labels on the two white buttons on the  bottom right of the Reports and Map screens are IMPOSSIBLE to read
Great app!! Any plans for adding support for receiving & reporting?
Excellent
Nice option for qrp portable stations
Works great..... i use vox and there is no physical connection between radio and phone.

Nice app... Map feature seems to gag up once in a while, but it's nice to set up my wspr beacon and an hour or so later, I can see what bands are going and where my signal is making it... Also good for comparing antennas... It was after deploying this that I realized my 150 foot longwire was kicking ass on 75 mtr

I use it for transmitting and monitoring WSPR using Yaesu and Icom radios via a SignaLink SL-1+ interface which handles the vox and audio isolation. Using it with a Samsung Galaxy S6 (Android 6.0.1) and a Samsung Tablet P5110 (Android 4.2.2) - works great. 73 G0SBN
As advertised, functions great with Wolphi link setup.
Great app and works beautifully. If it would run in the background and have an associated decoder it would be the ultimate for WSPR
Using with Wolphilink

A great tool that works well. My only gripe is it will transmit again after you have pressed stop. Its only a minor fault but it unexpectedly transmitted when I was swapping antennas,  that wasn't nice. Other than that WOW great app.
Great app.  Use it everyday.  Only issue I have with it is opening maps.  Very slow and seems buggy when panning around even though I'm using a fast phone.  Otherwise excellent app 5 stars
I love Android based digital modes.  This one is great for checking propagation.
For some reason, even though i have synced the time. It does no start TX until 17% through the cycle, and is that long over on the next cycle. Please help!

Been using the application for some time. Really great for checking Band Openings, switching between Antennas, and checking Station Performance. Only issue is that I have to manually Start and Stop transmission. Even if the program is "Stopped", it keys my transmitter. In addition, recently the WOLPHI INTERFACE causes my Transceiver to either Mute, or go into Transmit when plugged in. Rig is  Ten-Tec Model 535 Argonaut II (QRP). Otherwise, nice App.
Great App
I use this app for my qrp portable antenna and propagation testing. No need for a laptop!

This is the best - and of this writing, only - WSPR beacon in the app store.  Full marks for functionality on TX.  Upon pressing START my callsign shifts 1 to 2 chars over, but easily identified and fixed manually by the user.   The *only* reason this app did not get 5 stars is because it is transmit-only.  If the dev releases a fully-functional WSPR app in update (both transmit and receive) this will generate 5 stars for me. de N0LSD
Works great
A great tool that will help you understand propagation from your area .
Outstanding!  Works flawlessly!  Best ham radio app I've found         Dave W3WKP
It has been running all night without difficulty. Checked the map this morning & i am on it
Crappy
Awesome App!! I use WSPR BEACON with my Yaesu FT817ND and a long wire up 45 ft in a tree running 5 watts resulting in numerous contacts! Great job developer!!
I hooked this up to my KX3 and an indoor Alex Loop to see if it was getting out.  It was.  This is a simple and elegant program,  and we'll worth supporting

Really cool app. It is really neat to see visually on a map where your signal is going. Using a Yaesu FT 817 my 5 watt signal made it from Florida all the way to Germany and into the middle of South America.
Perfect for portable QRP
Thanks for all your time and effort with this app, 73 Colin DD5CF/G1ZOS
No fancy hookup or extensive wires needed. Uses the phone to generate tones and put your radio to VOX mode. Voila! Having lots of success with this. Worth every penny!

When I first loaded this App my callsign had to be typed in each time I started this App. I reported the problem.  Since this latest update my callsign and location are now permanently stored.  Mobile is the Note 3. Great App. Thanks. 73 Dick ZS6RO.

This developer understands very well then needs of man-portable operations like RaDAR and SOTA using and Android device. I am using the app with WolphiLink audio interface on samsung galaxy tab and samsung galaxy s4 both working flawlessly. Very well done highly recommended.
